g5101.definition: [τίς] probably emphatic of {{g5100}}; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what (in direct or indirect questions)

g5102.definition: [τίτλος] of Latin origin; a titulus or "title" (placard)

g5103.definition: [Τίτος] of Latin origin but uncertain significance; Titus, a Christian

g5104.definition: [τοί] probably for the dative case of {{g3588}}; an enclitic particle of asseveration by way of contrast; in sooth)

g5105.definition: [τοιγαροῦν] from {{g5104}} and {{g1063}} and {{g3767}}; truly for then, i.e. consequently

g5106.definition: [τοίνυν] from {{g5104}} and {{g3568}}; truly now, i.e. accordingly

g5107.definition: [τοιόσδε] (including the other inflections); from a derivative of 5104 and {{g1161}}; such-like then, i.e. so great

g5108.definition: [τοιοῦτος] (including the other inflections); from {{g5104}} and {{g3778}}; truly this, i.e. of this sort (to denote character or individuality)

g5110.definition: [τόκος] from the base of {{g5088}}; interest on money loaned (as a produce)

g5111.definition: [τολμάω] from τόλμα (boldness; probably itself from the base of {{g5056}} through the idea of extreme conduct); to venture (objectively or in act; while {{g2292}} is rather subjective or in feeling); by implication, to be courageous

g5112.definition: [τολμηρότερον] neuter of the compound of a derivative of the base of 5111 (as adverb); more daringly, i.e. with greater confidence than otherwise

g5114.definition: [τομώτερος] comparative of a derivative of the primary τέμνω (to cut; more comprehensive or decisive than {{g2875}}, as if by a single stroke; whereas that implies repeated blows, like hacking); more keen

g5115.definition: [τόξον] from the base of {{g5088}}; a bow (apparently as the simplest fabric)

g5116.definition: [τοπάζιον] neuter of a presumed derivative (alternately) of τόπαζος (a "topaz"; of uncertain origin); a gem, probably the chrysolite

g5117.definition: [τόπος] apparently a primary word; a spot (general in space, but limited by occupancy; whereas {{g5561}} is a large but participle locality), i.e. location (as a position, home, tract, etc.); figuratively, condition, opportunity; specially, a scabbard

g5118.definition: [τοσοῦτος] from τόσος (so much; apparently from {{g3588}} and {{g3739}}) and {{g3778}} (including its variations); so vast as this, i.e. such (in quantity, amount, number of space)

g5119.definition: [τότε] from (the neuter of) {{g3588}} and {{g3753}}; the when, i.e. at the time that (of the past or future, also in consecution)

g5120.definition: [τοῦ] properly, the genitive case of {{g3588}}; sometimes used for {{g5127}}; of this person

g5121.definition: [τοὐναντίον] contraction for the neuter of {{g3588}} and {{g1726}}; on the contrary

g5122.definition: [τοὔνομα] contraction for the neuter of {{g3588}} and {{g3686}}; the name (is)

g5124.definition: [τοῦτο] neuter singular nominative or accusative case of {{g3778}}; that thing

g5125.definition: [τούτοις] dative case plural masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; to (for, in, with or by) these (persons or things)

g5126.definition: [τοῦτον] accusative case singular masculine of {{g3778}}; this (person, as objective of verb or preposition)

g5127.definition: [τούτου] genitive case singular masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; of (from or concerning) this (person or thing)

g5128.definition: [τούτους] accusative case plural masculine of {{g3778}}; these (persons, as objective of verb or preposition)

g5129.definition: [τούτῳ] dative case singular masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; to (in, with or by) this (person or thing)

g5130.definition: [τούτων] genitive case plural masculine or neuter of {{g3778}}; of (from or concerning) these (persons or things)

g5131.definition: [τράγος] from the base of {{g5176}}; a he-goat (as a gnawer)

g5132.definition: [τράπεζα] probably contracted from {{g5064}} and {{g3979}}; a table or stool (as being four-legged), usually for food (figuratively, a meal); also a counter for money (figuratively, a broker's office for loans at interest)

g5134.definition: [τραῦμα] from the base of τιτρώσκω (to wound; akin to the base of {{g2352}}, {{g5147}}, {{g5149}}, etc.); a wound

g5136.definition: [τραχηλίζω] from {{g5137}}; to seize by the throat or neck, i.e. to expose the gullet of a victim for killing (generally, to lay bare)

g5137.definition: [τράχηλος] probably from {{g5143}} (through the idea of mobility); the throat (neck), i.e. (figuratively) life

g5138.definition: [τραχύς] perhaps strengthened from the base of {{g4486}} (as if jagged by rents); uneven, rocky (reefy)

g5139.definition: [Τραχωνῖτις] from a derivative of {{g5138}}; rough district; Trachonitis, a region of Syria

g5141.definition: [τρέμω] strengthened from a primary τρέω (to "dread", "terrify"); to "tremble" or fear

g5142.definition: [τρέφω] a primary verb (properly, τρέφω; but perhaps strengthened from the base of {{g5157}} through the idea of convolution); properly, to stiffen, i.e. fatten (by implication, to cherish (with food, etc.), pamper, rear)

g5143.definition: [τρέχω] apparently a primary verb (properly, θρέχω; compare {{g2359}}); which uses δρέμω (the base of {{g1408}}) as alternate in certain tenses; to run or walk hastily (literally or figuratively)

g5146.definition: [τρίβολος] from {{g5140}} and {{g956}}; properly, a crow-foot (three-pronged obstruction in war), i.e. (by analogy) a thorny plant (caltrop)

g5147.definition: [τρίβος] from τρίβω (to "rub"; akin to τείρω, τρύω, and the base of {{g5131}}, {{g5134}}); a rut or worn track

g5148.definition: [τριετία] from a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g2094}}; a three years' period (triennium)

g5149.definition: [τρίζω] apparently a primary verb; to creak (squeak), i.e. (by analogy) to grate the teeth (in frenzy)

g5150.definition: [τρίμηνον] neuter of a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g3376}} as noun; a three months' space

g5152.definition: [τρίστεγον] neuter of a compound of {{g5140}} and {{g4721}} as noun; a third roof (story)

g5153.definition: [τρισχίλιοι] from {{g5151}} and {{g5507}}; three times a thousand

g5154.definition: [τρίτος] ordinal from {{g5140}}; third; neuter (as noun) a third part, or (as adverb) a (or the) third time, thirdly

g5155.definition: [τρίχινος] from {{g2359}}; hairy, i.e. made of hair (mohair)

g5156.definition: [τρόμος] from {{g5141}}; a "trembling", i.e. quaking with fear

g5157.definition: [τροπή] from an apparently primary τρέπω to turn; a turn ("trope"), i.e. revolution (figuratively, variation)

g5158.definition: [τρόπος] from the same as {{g5157}}; a turn, i.e. (by implication) mode or style (especially with preposition or relative prefix as adverb, like); figuratively, deportment or character

g5159.definition: [τροποφορέω] from {{g5158}} and {{g5409}}; to endure one's habits

g5160.definition: [τροφή] from {{g5142}}; nourishment (literally or figuratively); by implication, rations (wages)

g5163.definition: [τροχιά] from {{g5164}}; a track (as a wheel-rut), i.e. (figuratively) a course of conduct

g5164.definition: [τροχός] from {{g5143}}; a wheel (as a runner), i.e. (figuratively) a circuit of physical effects

g5165.definition: [τρύβλιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of uncertain affinity; a bowl

g5166.definition: [τρυγάω] from a derivative of τρύγω (to dry) meaning ripe fruit (as if dry); to collect the vintage

g5167.definition: [τρυγών] from τρύζω (to murmur; akin to {{g5149}}, but denoting a duller sound); a turtle-dove (as cooing)

g5168.definition: [τρυμαλιά] from a derivative of τρύω (to wear away; akin to the base of {{g5134}}, {{g5147}} and {{g5176}}); an orifice, i.e. needle's eye Compare {{g5169}}.

g5169.definition: [τρύπημα] from a derivative of the base of {{g5168}}; an aperture, i.e. a needle's eye

g5170.definition: [Τρύφαινα] from {{g5172}}; luxurious; Tryphæna, a Christian woman

g5172.definition: [τρυφή] from θρύπτω (to break up or (figuratively) enfeeble, especially the mind and body by indulgence); effeminacy, i.e. luxury or debauchery

g5173.definition: [Τρυφῶσα] from {{g5172}}; luxuriating; Tryphosa, a Christian female

g5174.definition: [Τρωάς] from Τρός (a Trojan); the Troad (or plain of Troy), i.e. Troas, a place in Asia Minor

g5175.definition: [Τρωγύλλιον] of uncertain derivation; Trogyllium, a place in Asia Minor

g5176.definition: [τρώγω] probably strengthened from a collateral form of the base of {{g5134}} and {{g5147}} through the idea of corrosion or wear; or perhaps rather of a base of {{g5167}} and {{g5149}} through the idea of a craunching sound; to gnaw or chew, i.e. (generally) to eat

g5177.definition: [τυγχάνω] probably for an obsolete τύχω (for which the middle voice of another alternate τεύχω (to make ready or bring to pass) is used in certain tenses; akin to the base of {{g5088}} through the idea of effecting; properly, to affect; or (specially), to hit or light upon (as a mark to be reached), i.e. (transitively) to attain or secure an object or end, or (intransitively) to happen (as if meeting with); but in the latter application only impersonal (with {{g1487}}), i.e. perchance; or (present participle) as adjective, usual (as if commonly met with, with {{g3756}}, extraordinary), neuter (as adverb) perhaps; or (with another verb) as adverb, by accident (as it were) Compare {{g5180}}.

g5178.definition: [τυμπανίζω] from a derivative of {{g5180}} (meaning a drum, "tympanum"); to stretch on an instrument of torture resembling a drum, and thus beat to death

g5179.definition: [τύπος] from {{g5180}}; a die (as struck), i.e. (by implication) a stamp or scar; by analogy, a shape, i.e. a statue, (figuratively) style or resemblance; specially, a sampler ("type"), i.e. a model (for imitation) or instance (for warning)

g5180.definition: [τύπτω] a primary verb (in a strengthened form); to "thump", i.e. cudgel or pummel (properly, with a stick or bastinado), but in any case by repeated blows; thus differing from {{g3817}} and {{g3960}}, which denote a (usually single) blow with the hand or any instrument, or {{g4141}} with the fist (or a hammer), or {{g4474}} with the palm; as well as from {{g5177}}, an accidental collision); by implication, to punish; figuratively, to offend (the conscience)

g5181.definition: [Τύραννος] a provincial form of the derivative of the base of {{g2962}}; a "tyrant"; Tyrannus, an Ephesian

g5182.definition: [τυρβάζω] from τύρβη (Latin , a crowd; akin to {{g2351}}); to make "turbid", i.e. disturb

g5183.definition: [Τύριος] from {{g5184}}; a Tyrian, i.e. inhabitant of Tyrus

g5184.definition: [Τύρος] of Hebrew origin ({{h6865}}): Tyrus (i.e. Tsor), a place in Palestine

g5185.definition: [τυφλός] from, {{g5187}}; opaque (as if smoky), i.e. (by analogy) blind (physically or mentally)

g5186.definition: [τυφλόω] from {{g5185}}; to make blind, i.e. (figuratively) to obscure

g5187.definition: [τυφόω] from a derivative of {{g5188}}; to envelop with smoke, i.e. (figuratively) to inflate with self-conceit

g5188.definition: [τύφω] apparently a primary verb; to make a smoke, i.e. slowly consume without flame

g5189.definition: [τυφωνικός] from a derivative of {{g5188}}; stormy (as if smoky)

g5190.definition: [Τυχικός] from a derivative of {{g5177}}; fortuitous, i.e. fortunate; Tychicus, a Christian

g5192.definition: [ὑάκινθος] of uncertain derivation; the "hyacinth" or "jacinth", i.e. some gem of a deep blue color, probably the zirkon

g5194.definition: [ὕαλος] perhaps from the same as {{g5205}} (as being transparent like rain); glass

g5195.definition: [ὑβρίζω] from {{g5196}}; to exercise violence, i.e. abuse

g5196.definition: [ὕβρις] from {{g5228}}; insolence (as over-bearing), i.e. insult, injury

g5198.definition: [ὑγιαίνω] from {{g5199}}; to have sound health, i.e. be well (in body); figuratively, to be uncorrupt (true in doctrine)

g5199.definition: [ὑγιής] from the base of {{g837}}; healthy, i.e. well (in body); figuratively, true (in doctrine)

g5200.definition: [ὑγρός] from the base of {{g5205}}; wet (as if with rain), i.e. (by implication) sappy (fresh)
